article.description: — Tyrese Jenkins had a career-high 21 points as Norfolk State topped Delaware State 87-76 on Saturday.
article.headline: Jenkins carries Norfolk State past Delaware State 87-76
article.linkText: Jenkins carries Norfolk State past Delaware State 87-76
article.story: DOVER, Del. -- — Tyrese Jenkins had a career-high 21 points as Norfolk State topped Delaware State 87-76 on Saturday. Jenkins hit 5 of 6 3-pointers. Devante Carter had 15 points and eight assists for Norfolk State (7-4, 2-1 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). Joe Bryant Jr. added 15 points. Chris Ford had three blocks. Norfolk State posted a season-high 20 assists. Myles Carter had 20 points for the Hornets (0-8, 0-3), who have now lost eight consecutive games to start the season. Zach Kent added 15 points. Pinky Wiley had 14 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
